Liverpool of England stars Mohammed Salah of Egypt and Sadio Mane of Senegal will clash on Sunday in the grand final of the 33rd Africa Cup of Nations in Cameroon. The Pharaohs of Egypt ensured that by overcoming hosts Indomitable Lions of Cameroon this Thursday night, February 3, 2022 in a thrilling semi-final clash in Olembe. The match ended goalless after full and extra time, with Cameroon having two of their first four kicks saved by Egyptian goalkeeper Gabaski while the fourth was off target whereas the Pharaohs scored all theirs. Senegal had yesterday booked a place in the final by beating Burkina Faso 3-1 in the first semi-final. Cameroon will thus meet the Burkinabes in Saturday’s third-place match. Mohamed Salah, the Liverpool ace, has backed Egypt to win the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Cameroon. The Egyptian captain said the Pharaohs would give everything to win the 2021 AFCON trophy in Cameroon. Salah said this after leading his team to qualify for the AFCON quarter-final. Egypt… In "Sports" By Bushrah Yusuf-Badmus Ilorin  -  The Super Eagles have moved up in FIFA’s monthly world ranking, in spite of Nigeria’s inability to qualify for the just-ended 2017 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Gabon. In the ranking table the world football governing body released on Thursday, Nigeria moved up nine… In "Sports" Senegal reached a second consecutive Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) final on Wednesday after goals from Abdou Diallo, Idrissa Gueye and Sadio Mane secured a 3-1 win over Burkina Faso. Aliou Cisse’s side were denied a first AFCON title by Algeria back in 2019, but they will now have another chance against either Cameroon… In "Sports"